[I] Wuickly assembling 3d simulations, games, and visualization applications

[T] SimGear is a set of open-source libraries designed to be used as
[T] building blocks for quickly assembling 3d simulations, games, and
[T] visualization applications.
[T]
[T] SimGear is a relatively new project, and while quite a bit of code
[T] has been written in conjunction with the FlightGear project, the
[T] final interface and arrangements are still evolving.

[U] http://www.flightgear.org

